The above three conditions are then verified.

Once we have these sets, we define formula_84 if formula_85 for any formula_65; otherwise formula_87 for every formula_88, where formula_89 denotes the infimum. Using the fact that the dyadic rationals are dense, it is then not too hard to show that formula_31 is continuous and has the property formula_91 and formula_92 This step requires the formula_61 sets in order to work.

The Mizar project has completely formalised and automatically checked a proof of Urysohn&#x27;s lemma in the URYSOHN3 file.
